First Read: 05-Feb-26
HB405 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3
4 Relating to crimes and offenses; to add Section
5 13A-10-40.1 to the Code of Alabama 1975, to provide for the
6 crime of bail jumping in the third degree; and to provide
7 criminal penalties for violations.
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
9 Section 1. Section 13A-10-40.1 is added to the Code of
10 Alabama 1975, to read as follows:
11 §13A-10-40.1
12 (a) A person commits the crime of bail jumping in the
13 third degree if, having been lawfully released from custody,
14 with or without bail, upon condition that he or she is subject
15 to electronic monitoring, he or she violates any condition of
16 his or her court ordered electronic monitoring.
17 (b) It is a defense to prosecution under this section
18 that the defendant's violation was unintentional or was
19 unavoidable and due to circumstances beyond his or her
20 control. The burden of injecting the defense of an
21 unintentional violation, or unavoidability and circumstances
22 beyond his or control, is on the defendant.
23 (c) Bail jumping in the third degree is a Class C
24 misdemeanor.
25 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
26 1, 2026.
